The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | India thrash China
                                                                                                                       7                                      India thrash China
                      
	Salta (Argentina): An aggressive India thrashed China 4-1 in their second Group A match to inch closer to a semi-final berth in the Champions Challenge I hockey tournament here.         
	India, who led 2-0 at half time, now top the group jointly with New Zealand, who beat Belgium 4-1.         
	 India were promptly on the attack against China and earned a series of penalty corners.         
	They missed the first one but Prabhjot Singh was well positioned to collect the rebound on the second and he opened the scoring in the seventh minute Tuesday.         
	Rajpal Singh deflected the ball into the goal from close range to increase Indias lead to 2-0 in the 35th minute.         
	Sarwanjit Singh and Shivendra Singh scored the other two for India. (PTI)                                                                                                                     
